loud.name: ENGL Screamer 50 1x12 all-tube combo amp
loud.description: Selling my ENGL guitar amp because I recently moved to Texas and don’t have room for it in my apartment. 4 channels with built in reverb. Built like a tank and can get LOUD but still gives great tube sounds even at low volumes. It’s a very versatile amp — the clean channel is sparkling clean and each channel adds gain with metal tones achievable at the other end. I’ve been the only owner of this amp for the past 11 years and it’s only been gigged once or twice in that time. It’s essentially in mint condition. Let me know if you’d like to come try it out! text, call, or email is fine kevin

loud.name: VHT Standard 36 amp head
loud.description: Original Bay Area made VHT Standard 36 guitar amp head, $525, (lowered the price, time for it to go!)  This is in perfect condition, I played out with it a few times, but always kept it in good cover during transportation.  A really fine hand-wired powerful 36 watt amp.  I love this thing, but it gets really loud and I don't want to install a master volume.  It's a shame the local manufacturing couldn't keep this a profitable Bay Area amp.  I bought it after the company had closed locally.Read up about it, it's got four EL-84 tubes in the power amp, and two stages, really good cleans, really good grind when you crank it, and tons of articulation/ response from your guitar.  I purchased a couple variations of this amp, and I just don't play on this one enough.  I honestly think it's a bargain for the quality of tone it puts out.  I wanted it to replace my '73 Marshall, (r.i.p.) and it does a fine job.  It would be a shame for me to just keep it and not play on it.  Thanks,Dave  , text or email only please!

famous.name: Famous FS-1 Soprano Ukulele OBO
famous.description: Pretty little soprano, nice build with super-thin mahogany laminate, but with a sound that will rival most sold-wood ukes. Extremely light, with excellent projection and beautiful resonance. The FS-1 is a Japanese build, identical to the Kiwaya KS-1, but sold only to the Japanese market. This older uke has a Rosewood fingerboard, which you won't find in production any longer...the newer ones are walnut.  Nice, low action and great intonation. Friction tuners. Tiny scratch on the headstock, mark on the first fret - see the photos for detail. One-of-a-kind cloth gig bag included. Reasonable offers are welcome.

famous.name: 1880's Isidor Lot Wood Flute
famous.description: This flute was made by Isidor Lot, perhaps the nephew of the Famous flutemaker Louis Lotin the 1880's. It is openhole, inline G, C foot and was restored by Daniel Deitch in San Francisco.The sound is warm and sweet and has nothing to do with the volume of the 21st century.It comes in the original case.

Old music, really old music.  I don't have anything current.  Lots of classical and holiday.  There are books of opera, composers and more.  I also have a few books about famous composers.
